</opentopic:map><concept break-before="true" is-chapter="true" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " id="unique_1" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="history_of_paranormal_investigation" oid="history_of_paranormal_investigation" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">History of paranormal investigation</ph></title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Paranormal phenomena have captured the attention of the public and the sciences in
        different cultures throughout various eras of human history. The history reveals that
        methods and technologies of investigation are similar to those we use today. </shortdesc>
    <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Investigating unseen phenomena has a long history. When the topics become observable,
            paranormal investigation comes under the realm of science. In the 19th century many
            scientists, including Marie Curie, were interested in the paranormal. The development of
            technologies like the telegraph and phonograph lead to questions about the limits of
            time, space, and mortality. Projects of paranormal investigation are not typically
            considered within the realm of the professional sciences today. </p>
    </conbody>
</concept><concept break-before="true" is-chapter="true" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " id="unique_2" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="method_of_paranormal_investigation" oid="method_of_paranormal_investigation" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Method of paranormal investigation</ph></title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc "> Paranormal investigation can follow many different methods though they typically
        share similar features. Methods may include the use of people and technology to collect
        data.</shortdesc>
    <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
        <p class="- topic/p ">Many paranormal investigators use a scientific or pseudo-scientific methods in their
            investigation. Investigators each have their own methods which rely on technologies and
            human experiences. One common feature is carefully documenting experiences and movements
            to help in later debunking.   </p>
    </conbody>
<task class="- topic/topic task/task " id="unique_3" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="choose_investigation_site" oid="choose_investigation_site" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Choosing investigation site</ph></title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Choosing a place or person to investigate is an important task for paranormal
        investigation. Limited resources mean investigators must choose their site
        carefully.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
        <context class="- topic/section task/context ">Every site of an investigation is different and each investigator will have their
            own preferences.</context>
        <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Research the history of prospective locations including accounts previous
                    hauntings and investigations</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">List narratives and people of interest</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Consider technology needs</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Contact the site or person to introduce provided services and estimate date and
                    time of investigation</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Confirm logistical details and supply lists</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task><task class="- topic/topic task/task " id="unique_4" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="Conduct_exploratory_interview" oid="Conduct_exploratory_interview" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
    <title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph topic/title-wrapper ">Conducting exploratory interviews</ph></title>
    <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Exploratory interviews gather context about paranormal phenomena. </shortdesc>
    <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
        <context class="- topic/section task/context ">Interviews are a useful way to gather information about supposed experiences with
            paranormal phenomena. Speaking to those who experienced the phenomena can provide
            important context about the site and help determine if further investigation is needed. </context>
        <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Send survey to collect preliminary information about why they believe a
                    haunting is taking place</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Determine if investigation is necessary based on survey responses</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Contact interviewee(s) to set up a time and place to discuss their
                    experiences</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Develop specific, open-ended questions to gather additional information about experiences shared in the survey</cmd>
            </step>
            <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
                <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Meet with the participants and carefully document their answers</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task><task class="- topic/topic task/task " id="unique_5" topicrefclass="- map/topicref " nd:nd-id="Gather_data" oid="Gather_data" specializations="@props/deliveryTarget">
